  "description": "Herman Eugen Jeppsson was a Swedish doctor and municipal physician based in Halmstad. He was born on February 10, 1888, in S. Salle-rup, Malmöh, Sweden. His parents were Sven J. and Carolina Håkansson. Ingeborg Bæckström was his spouse, and they had a daughter named Cally, born in 1918. Jeppsson earned his Doctor of Medicine degree in 1906, Master of Philosophy in Medicine in 1907, and Bachelor of Medicine in 1910, all from Lund University. He obtained a Medical License in Stockholm in 1916. Throughout his career, Jeppsson served in various medical positions, including as assistant physician, military doctor, and municipal physician in Halmstad. He was also an assistant physician at epidemic hospitals in Stockholm and Halmstad. Jeppsson was a member of the Halmstad City Council and received the Order of the Royal Vasa."
